casebody.data:
Jean JAMISON, Appellant/Petitioner(s),
v.
HILLSBOROUGH COUNTY SHERIFF'S OFFICE, Appellee/Respondent(s). CASE NO.: 2D17-2953 District Court of Appeal of Florida, Second District. January 25, 2018

BY ORDER OF THE COURT:

The appellant's petition for all writs, treated within this appeal as a motion to compel, is denied. This appeal is dismissed for the appellant's failure to provide an appealable final order. This dismissal is without prejudice to the appellant to seek the issuance of a final order by filing a petition for writ of mandamus in this court.

NORTHCUTT, MORRIS, and BLACK, JJ., Concur.
